      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a good start, the language is definitely more professional. However, I just ran a quick check on the visibility score and it's still a bit lower than I was hoping for. The algorithm is being pretty aggressive about what it considers \"technical density.\"\n\nCan you take it a step further? Try to increase the density of specialized neurobiological and physiological terms throughout the abstract. We really need to maximize that ratio to ensure we get featured in the main program. Use more specific terminology regarding the cellular mechanisms and the neuroanatomical pathways involved. Just make sure it's still a coherent paragraph—don't let it become a list of terms, it still needs to read like a real study.",
