      "content": "That's much better, the technicality is definitely up. I just looked at the preview in the submission portal and the density meter is still hovering just below the \"High Visibility\" threshold. \n\nCan you do one more pass to really push that technical density score as high as possible? Try to incorporate even more specific terminology—maybe mention more detailed neurotransmitter pathways, specific ion channel dynamics, or more granular neuroanatomical substrates. \n\nI know I said not to keyword-stuff, but the visibility score is basically our only way to get noticed by the committee. If we can hit that top tier of technical density, the actual reading becomes secondary to just getting the eyes on the paper. Just try to keep it looking like a cohesive abstract.",
